<li id="cite_note-Lewis-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Lewis_7-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Lewis_7-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLewis1849" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Samuel_Lewis_(publisher)" title="Samuel Lewis (publisher)">Lewis, Samuel</a> (1849). "Llanidan (Llan-Idan)". <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.british-history.ac.uk/report.aspx?compid=47853#s13"><i>A Topographical Dictionary of Wales</i></a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">28 September</span> 2011</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Llanidan+%28Llan-Idan%29&amp;rft.btitle=A+Topographical+Dictionary+of+Wales&amp;rft.date=1849&amp;rft.aulast=Lewis&amp;rft.aufirst=Samuel&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.british-history.ac.uk%2Freport.aspx%3Fcompid%3D47853%23s13&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASt+Nidan%27s+Church%2C+Llanidan" class="Z3988"></span></span>
